Revision history for App-Lilu

0.01    Date/time
        First version, released on an unsuspecting world.
        - Added the baphomet EVE type (eve_type "baphomet"; event types
          found/banish/noted/alert/sighting/sighted), mirroring Lilith: a
          type=baphomet instance is tailed into baphomet_alerts (or pushed to
          the receiver). The offender IP maps to src_ip and a non-IP subject to
          its own column; only scalar fields become columns, the nested detail
          stays in raw. A top-level baphomet_event_ignore array drops chosen
          event types.
        - EVE field extraction factored out of the run() POE closure into a
          testable parse_eve() method, with %App::Lilu::alert_columns as the
          shared source of truth for each table's column order.
        - Fixed the sagan_alerts INSERT listing "proto" twice, which
          PostgreSQL rejects with "column specified more than once".
        - Added tests for new(), read_config(), eve_instances(),
          get_short_class_snmp(), and EVE parsing (Suricata/Sagan/CAPE).
        - Added optional push to a remote Lilith web receiver: with the new
          top-level lilith_url/lilith_apikey config, run() POSTs each parsed
          alert to <lilith_url>/eve/<table> via the new send_alert() method
          instead of inserting into a local database, so a sensor needs no DB
          credentials. dsn is no longer required when lilith_url is set. A
          lilith_verify_ssl option controls TLS certificate verification for an
          https receiver (default on).

